<br>
Apparently, Nortlav can rip through an unprepared force. Anyone have any other suggestions for fighting him?  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=286214">Nyaleen</a> Wickedwoe<BR>
Circle of Lemmings</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=viiperan>viiperan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/03 11:33:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.clanofone.com/ftpsite/macdill1-small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nortlav the Scalekeeper</span><hr size=1> Its a 1500pt lifetap.  Nortclav is pretty much same as vs although his melee appears higher and has a tendency to bounce around more.<br>
<br>
CH chain is not the best solution for this type fight.  A triple proc plus melee dmg can drop most tanks that are in this stage well before a ch lands in even a 3 sec chain. <br>
<br>
A rune chain with two+ chanters is the way to go.  With chain runes the MT is taking zero damgage so no need for heals.  If the rune gets eaten and the mt sees damage, he spams the raid channel its down and he needs heals.  Use quick heals till the next rune sets in, then the healers go back to nuking ;-)<br>
<br>
Edit: If he bounces around, you loose, he will heal himself up to fast for most small raid forces.  Be careful preping near him, he is not kos but will assist any golems that attack. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94501">Viiperan Deepfang</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Veteran Drow Warlord<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
Bristlebane</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=viiperan>viiperan</A> at: 4/4/03 11:36:06 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=romaandamorlita>RomaAndAmorlita</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/03 12:35:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nortlav the Scalekeeper</span><hr size=1> Omg, the name just makes me shiver. Yeah, he does a 1500 lifetap and my guild was in no way prepared for this fight. You need a chain rune cycle and people doing short, quick heals. Its pretty much the same deal as VS and Dracholich in Fear. For some reason our clerics didn't get the &quot;you can't CH on this mob&quot; idea down and we lost our tank(s) and rune-ers and it just got messy. He seemed to be harder than VS, but in any case u want nukers who can just toast this bastard fast <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Sage Roma Emeraldheart</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Level 65 Coercer<br>
The Arisen<br>
Terris-Thule<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=84333">Look Under My Dress</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Freddrick Transient</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Level 65 Overlord<br>
Dead Sexy Froaker<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=620383">Take Off My Pants</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=keaneabrams>Keane Abrams</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/03 1:10:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nortlav the Scalekeeper</span><hr size=1> Do NOT Defensive tank Nortlav. Your warrior needs to Evasive tank him. His lifetap is off a proc from his sword. No hit means no lifetap. Get him slowed and he is a gimp with evasive. Chain runing is not nececssary. One good chanter will be ok for runes. <br>
<br>
We did him 3 weeks ago with 3 groups ranging from 50 to 61. Have a couple healers always keep your tank above half health and you will be fine. <br>
<br>
One big key to keep in mind is that he will initially NOT con KoS. Don't let this fool you or your puller, he will assist any mob near him. So aggroing the flighty fiend that paths next to him will aggro him.<br>
<br>
Also, if you happen to catch Yael and Nortlav up at the same time, pull Yael first. And Yael is a total glorified orc pawn with a death touch. But thats for another thread.<br>
<br>
I recommend entering the area with Nortlav and Yael from the tunnel to the west. I have read that you can drop down the waterfall without aggroing mobs but it's not worth the risk imo.<br>
<br>
Good luck,<br>
<br>
